{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869105162,"sessionID":"ses_285f41dd6ffeYSA0uOwNOpslp8","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0c102d0018ADUzBrkGuuP1i","messageID":"msg_d7a0c02f20016LDYKcrStU7V4j","sessionID":"ses_285f41dd6ffeYSA0uOwNOpslp8","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_5dfb217493e647cca7bb1d90","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) providing `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` for creating code interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane).\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: AgentCube infrastructure consists of:\n12: - **Control Plane (Workload Manager)**: Session lifecycle management\n13: - **Data Plane (Router)**: Code execution and file operations\n14: \n15: Users need a Python client library to programmatically:\n16: 1. Create/manage Code Interpreter sessions\n17: 2. Execute commands and code remotely\n18: 3. Perform file operations (read/write/upload/download)\n19: 4. Invoke AgentRuntime workloads\n20: \n21: ### Goal\n22: \n23: Provide a well-designed Python SDK that:\n24: - Abstracts HTTP communication details\n25: - Handles session lifecycle automatically\n26: - Follows Python best practices (context managers, proper exceptions)\n27: - Supports both Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime use cases\n28: \n29: ### Value\n30: \n31: - **Developer Experience**: Simple `pip install agentcube-sdk` to get started\n32: - **Productivity**: High-level API vs raw HTTP calls\n33: - **Reliability**: Built-in retry, timeout, and error handling\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## Scope\n38: \n39: ### In-Scope\n40: \n41: | Component | Path | Description |\n42: |-----------|------|-------------|\n43: | Public API | `agentcube/__init__.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient` exports |\n44: | CodeInterpreterClient | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | Session lifecycle, command execution, file ops |\n45: | AgentRuntimeClient | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | Session bootstrap, payload invocation |\n46: | ControlPlaneClient | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | Session create/delete via Workload Manager |\n47: | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | Execute, files via Router |\n48: | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | Invoke via Router |\n49: | Utilities | `agentcube/utils/*.py` | HTTP session, token reading, logging |\n50: | Exceptions | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, etc. |\n51: | Tests | `tests/*.py` | Unit and integration tests |\n52: \n53: ### Out-of-Scope\n54: \n55: - Non-Python SDKs (Go, TypeScript, etc.)\n56: - Configuration dataclass (settings distributed across components)\n57: - Authentication beyond bearer token / service account file\n58: - Async support (future enhancement)\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## Impact Analysis\n63: \n64: ### Dependencies\n65: \n66: | Dependency | Purpose | Status |\n67: |------------|---------|--------|\n68: | `requests` | HTTP client | Required |\n69: | `PyJWT>=2.0.0` | JWT handling | Required |\n70: | `cryptography` | Crypto operations | Required |\n71: \n72: ### Upstream\n73: \n74: - `python-sdk/design.md` — Current design\n75: - `python-sdk/spec.md` — Specification requirements\n76: \n77: ### Downstream Consumers\n78: \n79: 1. **Python developers** — Using `agentcube-sdk` in their applications\n80: 2. **Internal services** — Agent execution workflows\n81: 3. **CLI toolkit** — Potential integration with CLI\n82: \n83: ### Risks\n84: \n85: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n86: |------|----------|------------|\n87: | Router/Workload Manager unavailable | Medium | Clear error messages, timeout handling |\n88: | Session expiration | Medium | Proper TTL handling, reconnection logic |\n89: | Network timeouts | Low | Configurable timeouts, retry logic |\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## Alternatives Considered\n94: \n95: ### Option 1: Use existing `openai` Python library (Not Selected)\n96: \n97: **Pros**: Familiar API\n98: **Cons**: Does not support AgentCube's custom session/header protocol\n99: \n100: ### Option 2: Generate SDK from OpenAPI spec (Not Selected)\n101: \n102: **Pros**: Automatic spec sync\n103: **Cons**: Spec not available; hand-crafted preferred for clarity\n104: \n105: ### Option 3: Single `Configuration` class (Not Selected)\n106: \n107: **Pros**: Centralized configuration\n108: **Cons**: Distributed defaults match existing deployment patterns better\n109: \n110: ### Option 4: Hand-crafted SDK (Selected)\n111: \n112: **Pros**: Full control over API design, clear documentation, follows spec exactly\n113: **Cons**: More implementation work\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ## Implementation Plan\n118: \n119: ### Phase 1: Core Infrastructure\n120: \n121: - [ ] Set up `pyproject.toml` with dependencies\n122: - [ ] Create package structure (`agentcube/`)\n123: - [ ] Implement exception hierarchy\n124: - [ ] Implement utilities (HTTP session, token reader, logger)\n125: \n126: ### Phase 2: Control Plane\n127: \n128: - [ ] Implement `ControlPlaneClient`\n129: - [ ] `create_session()` — POST to `/v1/code-interpreter`\n130: - [ ] `delete_session()` — DELETE with 404-as-success\n131: \n132: ### Phase 3: Data Plane — Code Interpreter\n133: \n134: - [ ] Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n135: - [ ] `execute_command()` — POST to `api/execute`\n136: - [ ] `run_code()` — Write .py file + execute\n137: - [ ] File operations: `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`\n138: \n139: ### Phase 4: High-Level Client\n140: \n141: - [ ] Implement `CodeInterpreterClient`\n142: - [ ] Context manager support (`__enter__`/`__exit__`)\n143: - [ ] Session lifecycle (create → init data plane → cleanup)\n144: \n145: ### Phase 5: Agent Runtime\n146: \n147: - [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n148: - [ ] `bootstrap_session_id()` — GET header inspection\n149: - [ ] `invoke()` — POST JSON payload\n150: - [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeClient`\n151: \n152: ### Phase 6: Testing\n153: \n154: - [ ] Unit tests for each client\n155: - [ ] Integration tests with mocked services\n156: - [ ] Example scripts (`examples/`)\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ## Acceptance Criteria\n161: \n162: ### CodeInterpreterClient\n163: \n164: | ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n165: |----|----------|-----------------|\n166: | CI-001 | Context manager exit | Session deleted, HTTP closed |\n167: | CI-002 | Missing router_url | ValueError raised |\n168: | CI-003 | Execute non-zero exit | CommandExecutionError raised |\n169: | CI-004 | Python code execution | Timestamped .py file created and executed |\n170: \n171: ### AgentRuntimeClient\n172: \n173: | ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n174: |----|----------|-----------------|\n175: | AR-001 | Context manager exit | HTTP session closed |\n176: | AR-002 | Missing session_id header | ValueError raised |\n177: | AR-003 | Invoke without session_id | ValueError raised |\n178: \n179: ### ControlPlaneClient\n180: \n181: | ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n182: |----|----------|-----------------|\n183: | CP-001 | Create session | Returns sessionId from response |\n184: | CP-002 | Delete 404 | Returns True |\n185: | CP-003 | Missing workload_manager_url | Uses WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var |\n186: \n187: ### DataPlaneClient\n188: \n189: | ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n190: |----|----------|-----------------|\n191: | DP-001 | Execute command | Returns stdout |\n192: | DP-001 | Upload file | Multipart POST with session header |\n193: \n194: ---\n195: \n196: ## Technical Design\n197: \n198: ### Public Exports\n199: \n200: ```python\n201: # agentcube/__init__.py\n202: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n203: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n204: \n205: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n206: ```\n207: \n208: ### CodeInterpreterClient\n209: \n210: ```python\n211: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n212:     def __init__(\n213:         self,\n214:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n215:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n216:         ttl: int = 3600,\n217:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n218:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n219:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n220:         verbose: bool = False,\n221:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n222:     ): ...\n223:     \n224:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n225:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n226:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n227:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n228:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n229:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\"): ...\n230:     def stop(self) -> None: ...\n231: ```\n232: \n233: ### Session Header\n234: \n235: All Router requests include:\n236: ```\n237: x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}\n238: ```\n239: \n240: ### Timeout Defaults\n241: \n242: - Read timeout: 120 seconds\n243: - Connect timeout: 5.0 seconds\n244: - Per-call override supported\n245: \n246: ---\n247: \n248: ## Timeline Estimate\n249: \n250: | Phase | Effort |\n251: |-------|--------|\n252: | Core Infrastructure | 1 hour |\n253: | Control Plane | 2 hours |\n254: | Data Plane (Code Interpreter) | 3 hours |\n255: | High-Level Client | 2 hours |\n256: | Agent Runtime | 2 hours |\n257: | Testing | 3 hours |\n258: | **Total** | **13 hours** |\n259: \n260: ---\n261: \n262: ## Existing Implementation Status\n263: \n264: Reference source: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`\n265: \n266: ### Package Layout\n267: \n268: | Path | Role |\n269: |------|------|\n270: | `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n271: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n272: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n273: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n274: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n275: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n276: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` |\n277: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n278: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` |\n279: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` |\n280: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |\n281: \n282: ### Current Gaps\n283: \n284: 1. **No implementation exists** — Need to create from scratch\n285: 2. **Testing infrastructure** — Need to set up test framework\n286: 3. **Examples** — Need to provide usage examples\n\n(End of file - total 286 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) providing `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` for creating code interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane).\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nAgentCube infrastructure consists of:\n- **Control Plane (Workload Manager)**: Session lifecycle management\n- **Data Plane (Router)**: Code execution and file operations\n\nUsers need a Python client library to programmatically:\n1. Create/manage Code Interpreter sessions\n2. Execute commands and code remotely\n3. Perform file operations (read/write/upload/download)\n4. Invoke AgentRuntime workloads\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775869105141,"end":1775869105158}}}}
