{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775869108598,"sessionID":"ses_285f41dd6ffeYSA0uOwNOpslp8","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0c2172001n0CNO8qCaFwy6i","messageID":"msg_d7a0c143a0014yvCvx59fEblDS","sessionID":"ses_285f41dd6ffeYSA0uOwNOpslp8","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869137232,"sessionID":"ses_285f41dd6ffeYSA0uOwNOpslp8","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0c2ccc001qeoJM8DmON3FVx","messageID":"msg_d7a0c143a0014yvCvx59fEblDS","sessionID":"ses_285f41dd6ffeYSA0uOwNOpslp8","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_0531a4775c9f4f028f0f77dc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement `AgentRuntimeClient` for the AgentCube Python SDK, enabling programmatic invocation of AgentRuntime workloads through the Router data plane with session bootstrap and JSON payload handling.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nAgentCube infrastructure consists of:\n- **Control Plane (Workload Manager)**: Session lifecycle management\n- **Data Plane (Router)**: Code execution and agent invocation\n\nThe `AgentRuntimeClient` complements `CodeInterpreterClient` (AR-027) by providing:\n1. Session bootstrapping via GET request to read `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n2. JSON payload invocation via POST with session header\n3. Context manager support for proper resource cleanup\n\n### Goal\n\nExtend the Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) with `AgentRuntimeClient` that:\n- Bootstraps session_id from the Router invocation endpoint\n- Supports session reuse via constructor argument\n- Provides clean context manager protocol\n- Follows existing SDK patterns (timeouts, logging, error handling)\n\n### Value\n\n- **Unified SDK**: Single package for both Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime\n- **Developer Experience**: Familiar high-level API\n- **Reliability**: Built-in session management, timeout handling\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| AgentRuntimeClient | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | High-level client API |\n| AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | Router communication |\n| Session bootstrap | `bootstrap_session_id()` | GET header extraction |\n| Invoke | `invoke()` | POST JSON payload |\n| Context manager | `__enter__`/`__exit__` | Resource cleanup |\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n\n- Changes to Control Plane (already covered in AR-027)\n- Authentication beyond existing token mechanism\n- Async support (future enhancement)\n- Non-Python SDKs\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose | Status |\n|------------|---------|--------|\n| `requests` | HTTP client | Required (from AR-027) |\n| `PyJWT>=2.0.0` | JWT handling | Required (from AR-027) |\n| `cryptography` | Crypto operations | Required (from AR-027) |\n\n### Upstream\n\n- `python-sdk/design.md` — Design specification\n- `python-sdk/spec.md` — Requirements (AgentRuntimeClient sections)\n- AR-027 — CodeInterpreterClient foundation\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **Python developers** — Invoking agent workloads\n2. **Agent orchestration** — Chaining multiple agent invocations\n3. **Internal services** — Agent execution workflows\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Router unavailable | Medium | Clear error messages, timeout handling |\n| Missing session header | Medium | ValueError with specific message |\n| Session expiration | Medium | Proper timeout handling |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Reuse CodeInterpreterClient structure (Not Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Familiar pattern\n**Cons**: Different use case (code execution vs agent invocation); separate concerns\n\n### Option 2: Generic \"AgentClient\" base class (Not Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Code sharing\n**Cons**: Over-engineering; clients have different initialization paths\n\n### Option 3: Standalone AgentRuntimeClient (Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Clear separation, follows existing SDK structure, easier to maintain\n**Cons**: Some code duplication with CodeInterpreterClient patterns\n\n### Option 4: Use existing HTTP libraries (httpx, aiohttp) (Not Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Async support potential\n**Cons**: Adds dependency; `requests` sufficient for sync use case\n\n---\n\n## Technical Design\n\n### AgentRuntimeClient\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n    ): ...\n\n    def __enter__(self): ...\n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n\n    def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n\n    def close(self) -> None: ...\n```\n\n### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        router_url: str,\n        namespace: str,\n        agent_name: str,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ): ...\n\n    def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n\n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n    ) -> requests.Response: ...\n\n    def close(self) -> None: ...\n```\n\n### Session Bootstrap Flow\n\n1. Client initialized with `agent_name`, `namespace`, `router_url`\n2. If `session_id` not provided, call `bootstrap_session_id()`:\n   - GET `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n   - Extract `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n   - Raise `ValueError` if header missing\n3. Store `session_id` for subsequent `invoke()` calls\n\n### Invocation Flow\n\n1. `invoke(payload, timeout)` validates `session_id` is set\n2. POST to base invocation URL with:\n   - Header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n   - Header: `Content-Type: application/json`\n   - Body: `json=payload`\n3. Return response (caller handles JSON parsing)\n\n### Session Header\n\nAll Router requests include:\n```\nx-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}\n```\n\n### Timeout Defaults\n\n- Read timeout: 120 seconds\n- Connect timeout: 5.0 seconds\n- Per-call override supported\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n- [ ] Implement `__init__` with router URL construction\n- [ ] Implement `bootstrap_session_id()` — GET + header extraction\n- [ ] Implement `invoke()` — POST JSON with session header\n- [ ] Implement `close()` — HTTP session cleanup\n\n### Phase 2: AgentRuntimeClient\n\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n- [ ] Implement `__init__` with session_id bootstrap\n- [ ] Implement `invoke()` — delegate to data plane\n- [ ] Implement context manager (`__enter__`/`__exit__`)\n- [ ] Implement `close()` — delegate to data plane\n\n### Phase 3: Integration\n\n- [ ] Update `agentcube/__init__.py` exports\n- [ ] Add examples (`examples/agent_runtime_usage.py`)\n- [ ] Add tests\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----|----------|-----------------|\n| AR-001 | Context manager exit | HTTP session closed |\n| AR-002 | Bootstrap without router | Uses ROUTER_URL env var |\n| AR-003 | Bootstrap missing session header | ValueError: \"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\" |\n| AR-004 | Invoke without session_id | ValueError: \"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\" |\n| AR-005 | Invoke with timeout | Uses (connect_timeout, timeout) tuple |\n| AR-006 | POST with correct headers | x-agentcube-session-id + Content-Type: application/json |\n\n---\n\n## Timeline Estimate\n\n| Phase | Effort |\n|-------|--------|\n| AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | 2 hours |\n| AgentRuntimeClient | 1.5 hours |\n| Integration & Tests | 2 hours |\n| **Total** | **5.5 hours** |\n\n---\n\n## Relationship to AR-027\n\nAR-027 (SDK CodeInterpreterClient) provides the foundation:\n- Package structure\n- Exception hierarchy\n- Utility modules\n- HTTP session management\n\nAR-028 extends this foundation with AgentRuntime-specific client, sharing:\n- `requests.Session` with pooling\n- Timeout conventions\n- Logger pattern\n- Exception classes","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775869137191,"end":1775869137229}}}}
